Diagnosis.
Female: Mesoscutellum with two barely noticeable protuberances; clypeus without yellow spot, if present, on lower half (

Fig. 
11

); labrum dark brown (

Fig. 
11

); basitibial plates elliptical; tegula yellowish brown, slightly translucent; metasoma orange or ferruginous, without metallic reflections (

Fig. 
12

), if present, then, metasoma with weak bluish metallic reflections and pubescence on mesosoma dark brown. Male: Distitarsi of hind leg with long and plumose hairs apically on ventral surface; hind claw with tuft of long, plumose hairs, mesoscutum and mesoscutellum widely covered by predominantly brown hairs (
Figs. 13, 14
); lateroinferior margin of labrum yellow or dark yellow (

Fig. 
13

).

Morphology. Female ( Figs. 11, 12 ). Measurements: body length: 24.4 ; head width: 7.3 ; thorax width: 9.6 ; forewing length: 19.7 ; UID: 2.9 ; LID: 3.3 ; mandible length: 3.1 ; mandible basal width: 1.4 ; labrum length: 1.1 ; labrum width: 2.1 ; F 1 length: 1.3 ; F 2 length: 0.3 ; F 3 length: 0.5 ; scape length: 0.9 ; diameter of median ocellus: 0.5 ; distance between lateral ocellus and eye: 0.6 . Coloration: Integument dark brown, except lower paraocular area and lateral margin of clypeus with yellow spot (
Fig. 11
). Tegula light brown to yellow, slightly translucent. Legs brown, lighter on hind tibia and tarsi (
Fig. 12
). Terga orange or ferruginous, without metallic reflections, if present, then metasoma dark brown with weak bluish metallic reflection. Sterna light brown. Wing membranes and veins brown, with very weak violaceous iridescence. Sculpture: Clypeus finely areolate with coarse, sparse punctures, scattered on disc. Labrum with coarse and dense punctures, except basally with very narrow smooth area. Terga finely areolate. T 1 with fine, very scattered punctures. T 2 and T 3 with fine, very sparse punctures (sparser than on T 1 ). T 4 and T 5 with coarser, denser punctures than on preceding terga. Pubescence: Labrum with yellow, plumose, dense pubescence, mixed with some light brown, simple hairs. Clypeus with dark brown, long, simple hairs on laterosuperior margin. Supraclypeal area and area near antennal socket with brown and yellowish hairs (
Fig. 11
). Gena with yellowish pubescence (
Fig. 12
). Vertex with dark brown hairs ( Figs. 11, 12 ). Mesoscutum, mesoscutellum and tegula with brown hairs with dark apices. Mesepisternum and propodeum with yellow pubescence (
Fig. 12
). Legs mainly with dark brown pubescence, except scopa yellow (
Fig. 12
). T 1 with yellow, long, plumose hairs. Fimbriae light orange. Structures: Mandible with four teeth of acute apex (length: 1 st> 2 nd> 4 th> 3 rd) (
Fig. 11
). Trimal angle well-developed, acute. Acetabular carina reaching base of fourth tooth. Clypeus almost uniformly convex (lateral view). Labrum elliptical. Vertex above upper interocular tangent. Inner orbits of compound eyes slightly converging dorsally (
Fig. 11
). Fore elaiospathe with secondary anterior comb formed by four giant, long, apically curved hairs. Mesoscutellum with barely noticeable protuberances, almost absent. Basitibial plates elliptical, secondary plate slightly projected backward, beyond posterior margin of primary plate. Pygidial plates with acute apex, primary plate with lateral margins straight.

Male ( Figs. 13, 14 ). Measurements : body length: 23.9 ; head width: 7.0; thorax width: 9.5 ; forewing length: 20.3 ; UID: 1.9 ; LID: 2.9 ; mandible length: 2.9 ; mandible basal width: 1.4 ; labrum length: 1.0; labrum width: 1.8 ; F 1 length: 1.3 ; F 2 length: 0.3 ; F 3 length: 0.4 ; scape length: 0.8 ; diameter of median ocellus: 0.5 ; distance between lateral ocellus and eye: 0.3 . Coloration: Integument dark brown, except yellow on lower paraocular area, labrum, anterior surface of scape and base of fore and middle tibiae ( Figs. 13, 14 ). Clypeus yellow with an inverted triangular dark brown spot (
Fig. 13
). Tegula light brown, slightly translucent. Legs brown, lighter on hind tibia and tarsi. Terga and sterna orange, without metallic reflections. Wing membranes light brown with very weak violaceous iridescence, veins brown. Sculpture: Clypeus areolate with coarse, relative uniform punctures. Labrum with coarse, dense punctures, without smooth upper area. Terga finely areolate. T 1 with fine, not very dense punctures. T 2 and T 3 with fine, dense punctures. T 4 and T 5 with coarser, scattered punctures than on preceding terga. Pubescence: Labrum with yellow, plumose, dense pubescence, mixed with some light brown, coarse, simple hairs. Clypeus with brown, long hairs on laterosuperior margin. Supraclypeal area and gena with yellowish pubescence ( Figs. 13, 14 ). Vertex with dark brown hairs (
Fig. 13
). Mesoscutum, tegula and area below wing base with brown hairs apically darker (
Fig. 13
). Mesoscutellum with yellow or brown hairs. Mesepisternum with both brown and yellow hairs (
Fig. 14
). Fore leg with light brown hairs, middle leg with dark brown pubescence, hind leg mainly with orange pilosity (
Fig. 14
). Base of claw of hind leg with long tuft of plumose hairs. Anterior surface of T 1 with yellowish hairs, brown on dorsal surface. T 2 and T 3 with brown, short, simple hairs. T 4 with similar pubescence, longer than on preceding terga. T 5 –T 7 and sterna with orange, long, plumose hairs. Structures: Mandible strongly curved apically with three teeth of acute apex ( 1 st> 2 nd> 3 rd) (
Fig. 13
). Third tooth with welldeveloped laminar projection. Trimal angle well-developed, straight. Acetabular carina reaching base of third tooth. Labrum elliptical. Vertex below upper inteocular tangent. Inner orbits of compound eyes converging dorsally (
Fig. 13
). Mesoscutellum with two barely noticeable protuberances, almost absent. Hind femur with protuberance on posterior surface. Anteroinferior margin of hind basitarsus with spine-like projection. Pygidial plate defined by lateral carinae.

Distribution. COLOMBIA : ANTIOQUIA: Amalfi, Andes, Apartadó, Medellín, Río Negro, Sabaneta MAGDALENA: El Campono, Parque Nacional Natural Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta . META : Villavicencio. RISARALDA: Pereira. VALLE DEL CAUCA: El Dovio (Vereda Bellavista). VAUPÉS: Taraira (Estación Biológica Mosiro Itájura Caparú) (
Fig. 17
).
